This paper discusses the use of social media metrics for measuring research impact, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as altmetrics are often used in this field for evaluating scholarly publications. The paper also touches upon topics related to social media and information retrieval (cs.IR), social computing (cs.SOC), and cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY). Additionally, the survey methodology used in the paper could be relevant to the sub-category of social informatics (cs.SI).
